# Scenario 003 - Linux Persistence Through Privileged Account Creation

## Overview

This scenario simulates an attacker who has already obtained administrative access to a Linux system and establishes long-term persistence by creating multiple privileged local accounts.

The objective is to generate detectable evidence of account creation, privilege assignment, and persistence mechanisms within the DarkForest SOC environment.

### Objectives

* Simulate persistence through account creation
* Generate account management telemetry
* Generate privilege assignment events
* Validate Splunk detection capabilities
* Verify dashboard visibility and investigation workflows

