## Lessons Learned

Persistence does not always require malware, scheduled tasks, or backdoors.

A compromised administrator can establish durable access simply by creating additional privileged accounts that blend into normal system administration activity.

```text
Compromised Administrator
         │
         ▼
Create Accounts
         │
         ▼
Grant sudo Access
         │
         ▼
Persistence Mechanism
         │
         ▼
Linux Audit Logs
         │
         ▼
Splunk Detection
```

This scenario demonstrates how account management telemetry can reveal persistence techniques and highlights the importance of monitoring privileged account creation and group membership modifications.
